## Summary

**What changed:**

• **`scripts/append_terminal_state_events.py`** — `lifecycle_for_scope()` now tracks session-scope runs (`phase: "session"`) in separate `session_run_started`/`session_run_completed` sets, computes `open_session_runs = session_run_started - session_run_completed`, and returns them as a 4th tuple element. `open_lifecycle()` passes the 4th element through (including fallback and ambiguous-reset paths). `append_terminal_events()` closes open session runs with `RunCompleted` carrying `outcome: "post_hoc_closed"`, returned as `completed_session_runs`.

• **`scripts/test_append_terminal_state_events.py`** — Updated existing test (renamed to `test_fallback_after_line_closes_open_agent_run_and_session_run`) to assert session runs ARE now closed with `post_hoc_closed`. Added two new tests: `test_closes_session_scope_orphan_run` (session RunStarted without RunCompleted gets closed) and `test_does_not_double_close_completed_session_run` (already-completed session runs are left alone).

**Verification:**
• All 9 unit tests pass (`python3 -m unittest scripts.test_append_terminal_state_events`)
• `--help` parses correctly
• `cargo fmt -- --check` clean

